# 5. CROSS JOIN

### Business Scenario

Generate every Product-Color combination.

### Query

```sql
SELECT
    p.Product,
    c.Color
FROM Products p
CROSS JOIN Colors c;
```

### Formula

```
Rows Returned = Rows in Table A × Rows in Table B
```

Example:

```
Products = 2
Colors = 3

Result = 2 × 3 = 6 rows
```

---

# 6. Finding Customers Without Orders

### Business Scenario

Identify customers who have never placed an order.

### Query

```sql
SELECT
    c.CustomerID,
    c.CustomerName
FROM Customers c
LEFT JOIN Orders o
    ON c.CustomerID = o.CustomerID
WHERE o.CustomerID IS NULL;
```

